
# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# [optional body: explain what and why, wrapped at 72 columns]
#
# ---- Commit conventions for this repository ----
# Format: Conventional Commits 1.0.0, written in English.
#
# type:  feat | fix | docs | refactor | chore | test | ci
#
# scope: the name(s) of the modified skill(s).
#   - one skill        -> feat(skill-authoring): add scaffold checklist
#   - several skills   -> fix(knowledge-sync, skill-authoring): align paths
#   - no specific skill, or a sweeping change across many skills
#                      -> omit the scope: chore: update catalog layout
#
# subject: imperative mood, no trailing period.
#
# Use a body when the change needs context (why, trade-offs, follow-ups);
# a subject line alone is fine for small, self-explanatory changes.
